ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC PRINQUAL <options> ; 
    TRANSFORM transform(variables </ t-options>)
    <transform(variables </ t-options>) ...> ; 
    ID variables ; 
    FREQ variable ; 
    WEIGHT variable ; 
    BY variables ; 

The PRINQUAL procedure performs principal component analysis (PCA) of qualitative, quantitative, 
or mixed data.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: ID variables ; 

The ID statement includes additional character or numeric variables in the output data set. 
The variables must be contained in the input data set.

Syntax: TRANSFORM transform(variables </ t-options>) <transform(variables </ t-options>) ...> ;

The TRANSFORM statement lists the variables to be analyzed (variables) and specifies the 
transformation (transform) to apply to each variable listed.
